      4 - Web server : it also uses HTTP/HTTPS protocol 
          Suppose we request something from the server it uses http or https protocol.
          
		  HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol):  is used for sending and receiving web content. It’s unencrypted.
          
		  HTTPS (HTTP Secure) : is the secure version of HTTP. It encrypts the data to protect it during 
		  transmission.
		  
		  How It Works:

		When you enter a URL like youtube.com in your browser, the request typically starts with HTTP or HTTPS, 
		depending on whether the site supports encryption.

		If the site supports HTTPS, your browser will initiate a secure connection. The request to the server
		and the response from the server are both encrypted using HTTPS.

		If the site only supports HTTP, the request and response are not encrypted.
		
		When you type youtube.com in your browser, the browser checks if the website supports HTTPS. If it does,
		it will use HTTPS to securely request and receive the website content. If not, it will use HTTP.
		
