Q6 : What is Domain name system ? 
Ans : A domain name is a user-friendly address for websites, like www.example.com, that replaces 
	  hard-to-remember IP addresses (e.g., 192.168.1.1). The Domain Name System (DNS) converts these domain names
	  into IP addresses so that users can easily access websites by typing the name instead of the numbers.
	  
	  If domain name does not work than write the ip address and you can get your website, but remembering domain
      is more easy than remebering IP address.	  
	  
      	             
